



A Transformer architecture is used to understand and  capture relationships between tokens in a sequence and process and then generate the language. A Transformer is an AI model architecture that learns the meaning of text by paying attention to important words and their relationships within a sentence.
 Types of Transformer Architecture
There are 3 type:
1. Encoder-Only Transformer Architecture
2.Decoder-only Transformer  Architecture
3.Encoder and Decoder Only Transformer Architecture

1.Encoder-Only Transformer Architecture: Encoder-only transformers focuses on understanding the meaning and context of input text.
Example: BERT 
